# Inventory Movement Log — Implementation Plan

Every stock change (sale, return, purchase, manual adjust, shrinkage) is recorded in a `stock_movements` table. A dedicated page shows the history with product-level drill-down and CSV export.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Database (Supabase SQL)

```sql
CREATE TABLE stock_movements (
  id           UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  product_id   UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES products(id),
  product_name TEXT NOT NULL,               -- snapshot at time of movement
  sku          TEXT NOT NULL,
  type         TEXT NOT NULL                -- 'SALE' | 'RETURN' | 'PURCHASE' | 'ADJUSTMENT' | 'SHRINKAGE'
    CHECK (type IN ('SALE','RETURN','PURCHASE','ADJUSTMENT','SHRINKAGE')),
  qty_before   INT NOT NULL,
  qty_change   INT NOT NULL,                -- negative for exits, positive for entries
  qty_after    INT NOT NULL,
  reason       TEXT,                        -- mandatory for ADJUSTMENT/SHRINKAGE
  reference_id UUID,                        -- sale_id, invoice_id, etc. (optional)
  created_by   UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  seller_name  TEXT,
  created_at   TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

ALTER TABLE stock_movements ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
CREATE POLICY "auth users can do all on stock_movements"
  ON stock_movements FOR ALL USING (auth.role() = 'authenticated');
```

